&lt;p&gt;The Security Manager is responsible for the protection of all hotel occupants, physical premises, guest and employee property, and the company&#39;s assets and reputation. This role involves managing the security team, enforcing policies, conducting investigations, and coordinating emergency responses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Security Operations &amp;amp; Management: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, implement, and enforce comprehensive security and safety policies, procedures, and standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the daily operations of the security department, including scheduling, patrols, and deployment of security team members (in-house or contracted).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular patrols and inspections of the premises to identify and mitigate potential risks and hazards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the functionality and maintenance of all security systems, including CCTV, access control systems (keys, key cards), and alarm systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement measures to prevent theft, pilferage, and unauthorized access to property assets, including cash, stock, and equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage key control procedures, including master keys and employee access cards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with local law enforcement, fire departments, and other external security services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and control access for contractors, suppliers, and vendors working on the property.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incident Response and Investigation: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond immediately to all security and safety-related incidents, emergencies, and guest/employee concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary decision-maker and coordinator during security incidents and emergencies (e.g., fire, medical, natural disasters, threats).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough investigations, gather evidence, and accurately document all security incidents, accidents, and property loss.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate emergency response measures, including medical assistance (first aid/CPR), fire evacuation, and crisis management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage the hotel&#39;s emergency response and crisis management plans, including conducting regular drills and training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle guest concerns, complaints, and security-related issues with professionalism and discretion, always prioritizing guest safety and comfort.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Training and Team Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit, train, supervise, and evaluate the performance of the security team ensuring professional and courteous service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide security and safety awareness training to all hotel staff across various departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the security team maintains professionalism and provides courteous service to guests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safety and Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the hotel is compliant with all local, provincial, and federal security, fire, and life safety regulations (e.g., OSHA, local fire codes).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with other department heads (e.g., General Manager, HR, Engineering) to ensure a holistic approach to safety and security.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in the Joint Health &amp;amp; Safety Committee Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee internal control procedures, especially those related to cash handling and high-value assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Administration and Budgeting:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the departmental budget, including expenditures for security equipment and labour.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of all security activities, incidents, and investigations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience (3+ years) in a security management or supervisory role, preferably within a hotel or hospitality environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A background in law enforcement, military, or a related security field is highly valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Certifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant security certifications (e.g., Certified Protection Professional - CPP, Certified Security Manager - CSM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First Aid, CPR, and AED certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant local/provincial security guard licensing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Competencies:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Leadership and Team Management:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ability to guide, train, and motivate a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Decision-Making:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ability to think quickly, remain calm, and make sound, objective decisions under pressure in emergency situations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Investigative Skills:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;Strong ability to conduct thorough investigations, gather evidence, and write comprehensive reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Technical Knowledge:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;Familiarity with modern security technologies, including CCTV, access control systems, and alarm systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Interpersonal Skills:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;Excellent written and verbal communication skills to interact effectively with guests, staff, management, and external authorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Integrity:&lt;/u&gt; High level of professionalism and discretion when handling confidential and sensitive information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nobu Hotel Toronto is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. If contacted for an employment opportunity, please advise Human Resources if you require accommodation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nobutorontojobs.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(160, 146, 112);&quot;&gt;VEW ALL JOBS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking a talented and enthusiastic individual to join our Hotel Lounge / In-Room Dining culinary team as a full-time Commis Chef. In this entry-level role, you will have the opportunity to learn and grow under the guidance of experienced chefs, to assist in the preparation and execution of the hotel&#39;s breakfast and all-day dining dishes. If you are passionate about fine dining, eager to develop your culinary skills, and committed to excellence in every dish you prepare, we invite you to join us at Nobu Hotel Toronto.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting in the preparation and cooking of various dishes according to established recipes and standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining high standards of food quality, freshness, and presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that all kitchen areas and equipment are clean, sanitized, and organized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with inventory management and stock control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Following proper food safety and hygiene practices at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with other kitchen colleagues to streamline workflow and maximize efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking direction from senior kitchen colleagues and executing tasks promptly and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhering to all company policies, procedures, and guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working in a professional kitchen environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Culinary school diploma or relevant certification preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong passion for food and cooking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent teamwork and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Food Handler certification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work flexible shifts including early mornings, evenings, weekends, and holidays as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of kitchen equipment and utensils.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and commitment to maintaining high standards of cleanliness and hygiene.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to stand for extended periods and lift heavy objects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team and be part of an exciting culinary journey! If you meet the above requirements and are eager to contribute your talents to our kitchen, please submit your application including your resume detailing your relevant experience. We look forward to hearing from you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nobu Hotel Toronto is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. If contacted for an employment opportunity, please advise Human Resources if you require accommodation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nobutorontojobs.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(160, 146, 112);&quot;&gt;VEW ALL JOBS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking a skilled and experienced full-time Sushi Chef to join our culinary team at Nobu Hotel and Restaurant, Toronto. In this key role, you will be responsible for the preparation, assembly, and presentation of sushi and sashimi dishes, ensuring the highest standards of quality, flavour, and presentation. If you are passionate about Japanese cuisine, have a strong foundation in sushi preparation techniques, and thrive in a fast-paced kitchen environment, we invite you to join us at Nobu and showcase your talent as a Sushi Chef.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and assemble a variety of sushi and sashimi dishes, including nigiri, maki rolls, and specialty rolls, according to Nobu&#39;s recipes and standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the highest standards of quality, freshness, and flavour in all sushi preparations, using the freshest seafood, vegetables, and other ingredients available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with the sushi team to prioritize orders, expedite service, and maintain efficient flow and timing during busy service periods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain cleanliness, organization, and sanitation in the sushi bar area, including workstations, equipment, utensils, and storage areas, in accordance with health and safety regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory levels, track usage, and assist with ordering and receiving of seafood and other ingredients to ensure availability and freshness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train and mentor junior sushi chefs, sushi apprentices, and kitchen assistants in sushi preparation techniques, knife skills, and food safety procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other members of the culinary team, including sous chefs, line cooks, and pastry chefs, to ensure smooth and efficient operation of the kitchen and timely delivery of orders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace Nobu&#39;s commitment to innovation, creativity, and excellence in sushi preparation, and contribute ideas for new menu items, specials, and promotions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience as a sushi chef in a fine-dining restaurant or sushi bar environment, with a strong foundation in sushi preparation techniques, knife skills, and sushi bar operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive knowledge of seafood varieties, sushi rice preparation, and traditional and contemporary sushi styles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work efficiently and effectively in a fast-paced kitchen environment, with strong organizational and time management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and teamwork abilities, with the ability to collaborate effectively with other members of the culinary team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work evenings, weekends, and holidays as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be legally eligible to work in Canada.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team and be part of an exciting culinary journey! If you meet the above requirements and are eager to contribute your talents to our kitchen, please submit your application including your resume detailing your relevant experience. We look forward to hearing from you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nobu Hotel Toronto is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. If contacted for an employment opportunity, please advise Human Resources if you require accommodation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nobutorontojobs.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(160, 146, 112);&quot;&gt;VEW ALL JOBS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking talented and passionate individuals to join our team as a full-time Bartender. In this exciting role, you will be responsible for crafting and serving exceptional cocktails, providing attentive service to guests, and creating memorable experiences in our bar area. If you are a skilled mixologist, have a passion for hospitality, and thrive in a fast-paced environment, we invite you to join us at Nobu and showcase your talent behind the bar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and serve a variety of cocktails, spirits, and other beverages in accordance with Nobu&#39;s standards and recipes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with guests in a friendly and professional manner, providing personalized recommendations and ensuring an exceptional experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate expert knowledge of mixology techniques, cocktail ingredients, and beverage offerings, including Nobu&#39;s signature drinks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain cleanliness and organization of the bar area, including bar tools, glassware, and ingredients, in compliance with health and safety regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process guest orders accurately and efficiently, handling cash transactions and maintaining an orderly cash register.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory levels and restock supplies as needed to ensure smooth operations during peak hours.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other team members, including servers, kitchen staff, and management, to ensure seamless coordination and exceptional service delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to all alcohol laws and regulations, promoting responsible serving practices and ensuring guest safety at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of bartending experience in a high-volume, upscale establishment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive knowledge of cocktails, spirits, and mixology techniques, with a passion for creating innovative and memorable drinks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong customer service skills, with the ability to engage with guests in a warm and welcoming manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work effectively as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and precision in preparing drinks, maintaining cleanliness, and upholding quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work evenings, weekends, and holidays as required by the demands of the hospitality industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification in responsible alcohol service (e.g., Smart Serve) is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nobu Hotel Toronto is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. If contacted for an employment opportunity, please advise Human Resources if you require accommodation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nobutorontojobs.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(160, 146, 112);&quot;&gt;VEW ALL JOBS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking a talented and passionate individual to join our culinary team as a full-time Pastry Commis Chef at Nobu Hotel Toronto. In this entry-level role, you will have the opportunity to learn and grow under the guidance of experienced pastry chefs while contributing to the preparation and creation of Nobu&#39;s exquisite pastry offerings. If you are creative, detail-oriented, and eager to develop your skills, we invite you to join us at Nobu and be part of our renowned culinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and production of a variety of pastry items, including cakes, tarts, desserts, and breads, under the guidance of senior pastry chefs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow Nobu&#39;s recipes, standards, and techniques to ensure consistency and quality in all pastry preparations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle basic pastry techniques such as mixing, shaping, baking, and decorating with precision and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain cleanliness, organization, and sanitation in the pastry kitchen area, including workstations, equipment, utensils, and storage areas, in accordance with health and safety regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with inventory management, including tracking ingredient usage, restocking supplies, and rotating stock to ensure freshness and minimize waste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other members of the pastry team to ensure smooth and efficient operation of the pastry kitchen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace Nobu&#39;s commitment to innovation and creativity in pastry arts, and contribute ideas for new menu items, specials, and promotions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn and develop pastry skills and knowledge through training, mentorship, and hands-on experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhering to all company policies, procedures, and guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience working in a professional kitchen environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Culinary school diploma or relevant certification preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong passion for food and cooking/baking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work well under pressure in a high-volume fine dining kitchen environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent teamwork and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to work evenings, weekends, and holidays as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of kitchen equipment and utensils.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and commitment to maintaining high standards of cleanliness and hygiene.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to stand for extended periods and lift heavy objects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our team and be part of an exciting culinary journey! If you meet the above requirements and are eager to contribute your talents to our kitchen, please submit your application including your resume detailing your relevant experience. We look forward to hearing from you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nobu Hotel Toronto is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. If contacted for an employment opportunity, please advise Human Resources if you require accommodation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nobutorontojobs.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(160, 146, 112);&quot;&gt;VEW ALL JOBS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

